				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Now normally I don't do this.. however, I also believe it's important for SOE to get an idea of the inpact OOW is having in our little corner of Norrath.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Special Rules apply to this thread</span>.. if you have cancelled your account as a direct result of the last 2 weeks then feel free to add your name.  Feel free to explain why you have done so. However hysteria will not help. Please <span style="text-decoration: underline">remain factful and respectful</span> and <span style="text-decoration: underline">don't resort to SOE bashing</span>.. it's old and boring. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">If you disagree with someone's reasoning,</span> please go ahead and start a new thread don't add to this one. You can even disagree that I'm making a place for this list, that's fine. 
<br />

<br />
I wish this thread to be a place for fellow Enchanters to speak their minds. SOE has every right to not want a lot of negative SOE threads on their boards. I'm also entitled to allow a place to show them the inpact that these changes are having on their wallets and the community we have all worked so hard to build. 
<br />

<br />
Here is my commentary (which I very rarely add BTW)
<br />

<br />
IMO, it seems that it's more than the charm changes.. our epic (lack of thought in the effect/focii) , the lack of a clear direction for Enchanters in their spell lines, the order in which our spells are given to use on Rune turn in.. all of these things seem to be pointing in one direction --> Is anyone listening? The only thing worse than not listening is saying you are, then ignoring the feedback. 
<br />

<br />
Please share this link with other enchanters who would like to have their status known to SOE.<br />_________________<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Quote of the Week:</span> 
<br />
<span style="color: darkblue"><span style="font-style: italic">"Caution: Cape does not enable user to fly."</span>
<br />
-Batman Costume warning label</span>
<br />

