			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My accounts are not yet canceled.  I am being patient and giving a short period of time for something dramatic to be done.  If nothing is done after that, i will probably cancel only the enchanter account and try to play another character at least until a few months after the release of wow.  Enchanters have nothing to offer of use except for c, and i can get that at anytime with another character from the pok kei-bots without the need to pay the monthly fee.  Even though that fee is a trivial amount for me, enchanters are so worthless at this point that i feel no use can be derived from the char that offsets even the pittance required to maintain the account.
<br />

<br />
The developers either a) don't even bother testing with enchanter characters or b) are so completely out of touch with the game they don't realize the fundamental gameplay changes that have occurred since the oldworld zones/kunark.  Having been further in content than most, i have seen what is now occurring for many people several months ago.  I think the developers, as many of the players in older content, didn't realize that mezzing as a means of cc has been doomed to failure and has been an anachronism since shortly after the release of pop (with the possible exception of ldon).  It was difficult to realize exactly how weak the enchanter class was sans charm and in an environment with easy single-pullable outdoor zones.
<br />

<br />
Enchanters have been tuned around having super-powerful pets.  Our other abilities, to put it bluntly, suck.  In exchange we've been dps gods in a limited number of situations.  Now, only one side of that equation has changed.  The positive side is gone with the nerfs.  The poor quality of the other abilities remains.  In fact, with the removal of wom and the change to lull enchanter abilities have gotten even worse.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a> (retired)
<br />
-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1192270" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pojke</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
