			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had two accounts and canceled them both.  This last nerf was the icing on the cake for me.
<br />

<br />
My reasons:
<br />

<br />
We have no role in group.  None.  We’re not DPS (and no, this charm is not viable for DPS when the RvR is so unbalanced) and we’re no longer a CC class.  I did not make my enchanter to become relegated to the role of buff bot and with OoW, that’s exactly what I have become.
<br />

<br />
I’ve seen our abilities watered down so much that we’re not wanted or needed in most groups.  There is very little need for CC, for two basic reasons.  First cc is done on the pull – resulting in single mobs in camp.  In the event that there are multiple mobs, the MR on them is so high, they hit so hard and fast, that cc is best done by bards who can mez and take hits far better than enchanters, shaman who can root, and again take hits far better than enchanters, paladins who can offtank, etc.  The enchanter is no longer a CC class
<br />

<br />
Charm was one tool, the only tool, that we had that made soloing an option.  It was also an attractive tool that we had, which made us desirable for groups, since CC no longer was.  Then came the nerfs – the 4 person aggro rule, the MR adjustment to the mobs, the MR adjustment to CoD, the experience nerf, the “charm immune” flag in many zones, the lack of mobs to charm in specific zones (LDON’s with only 1 type of mob charmable), etc    We weren’t happy, but we understood the reasons why this happened and we dealt with it
<br />

<br />
Then OoW  where our charms were nerfed once again.  Our class has been reduced to nothing more than a buff class.  Groups have no desire to have an enchanter there to charm.  It brings nothing to the group but an increased risk for a wipe.  Before at least (not including Tipt/Vxed) there was a return seen for using a charmed pet, this is no longer the case
<br />

<br />
(I repeated myself a bit,,, but I’m in a hurry,, will try to clean it up later)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
