			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have cancelled my 2 accounts as of 9/23.  My main reason is that our role in this game is slowly being taken away.  As Brenlo aptly stated, as we continue to scale mobs up faster than players, we cant allow enchanters to charm.  The scaling up of mobs faster than players basically means the end of the enchanter class and our skills.
<br />

<br />
1.  Charm.  They cant let us continue to charm because as the mobs scale up faster than players....there will continue to be a higher dps widening betwen what players can do and what a charm mob will do.  So basically charm is dead if they continue down this path of scaling up mobs faster than players.
<br />

<br />
2.  Mezz.  In the same token as above, it has become extremely dangerous to mez these scaled up mobs.  What we have seen is tank mez.  It is much safer to mez with a tank/healer than with us.  Even if the spells are still there....as they scale up the mobs faster than they scale us up...most people will come to realize...it is not worth the risk for an enchanter to mez...we are <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> going to be <span style="font-weight: bold">dependable</span> in doing this...one resist may wipe the raid....better to go with a tank/healer.  The spacing of mobs in Omens suggests to me that it was designed to be done <span style="font-weight: bold">WITHOUT </span>the need for CC.
<br />

<br />
3.  Fear.  This was eliminated a long time ago (no fear after 55).  Most enchanters I dont think even realized this.  I grew up with reverse kiting with a druid and use this to level to 30 in rathe mtn pre kunark.
<br />

<br />
4.  Buffs.  We still have these.  Though most of these can be made up by other classes except the clarity line (but you really only need a buff bot for this skill).
<br />

<br />
5. Debuffs.  Even though we may still have the best slow.  It casts slower and its all magic based.  Other classes are not far behind and can slow alot fast than us.  Cripple and recant magic....other classes can also do.
<br />

<br />
6. Stun.  And pre kunark, I use to have 2 of these loaded at all times.  And now, Color cloud in very specific situations.  Other classes stun better.  We lost this a long time ago.
<br />

<br />
7.  Nukes.  If you had to depend on our nuking to win an event, you better go find one wizzy (who can probably replace 5 of us).  If it is a high MR mob, we have no other alternatives....we are just spectators (wonder if that can be a new class....convert all enchanters to spectators)
<br />

<br />
So basically we are reduced to buffbots.  I dont find playing a buffbot particularly challenging.  It is very disturbing that we dont even have a class description.  I get the feeling that SOE felt that the enchanter class was created in error....they have been doing their best to eliminate this mistake for a long time.  We were either too overpowering for an encounter or trivial (when they tag everything non charmable, non stunable and non mezzable).  There didnt appear to be a middle ground with us...maybe it was too hard to program.  It is also interesting to note that in EQ II....our class has been split in 2....you cant mez and charm.
<br />

<br />
It was good while it lasted....I LOVED THIS CLASS.
<br />
Skil
<br />
66 Enchanter
<br />
Cazic-Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
