			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have been playing my enchanter since 1999, and consider myself a very casual player.  I explored alot ventured all over to see what I could see, playing an enchanter gave me the ability to go just about anywhere and interact with the NPCs of the world.  I've never been an XP grinder.  I prefer to kill the big stuff.  I plowed through PoP getting all of my flags/keys (never had a flag buddy flag me).  Took awhile but I am in a great guild that has a good progression schedule. 
<br />

<br />
GoD comes out.....  Another f'ing flag fest!  Another round of mobs that hit like trucks and resists randomly.  No lore to speak of, just a bunch of zones filled with things that hate you, and nothing to do but kill everything or get killed.  I got fed up, and said "Fine, I'll sit this one out. The PoP flagging burned me out, and if I am going to keep playing this game, I need a break."  
<br />

<br />
Now OoW comes out....  Not a Flag/Key hell expansion!  YEAH! I look at the Charm changes and say "Well, it's to keep from having chanters charming big NPCs and racking in the XP."  Then I look at mezzing "We don't even mezz anymore because getting the single pull is a hell of alot better then the random resists chanters get."  Now I look at raid aspects "I can be DPS... no, charms are weak and our spell DPS is just funny.  I can do mezzing... no, mobs are pulled single or offtanked because our mezzing isn't reliable.  I can do buffing... no, it's a raid we have 5 enchanters only really need one to do that."  
<br />

<br />
So now I'm stuck.  I'm a raid enchanter that can't provide any uses in a raid situation.  I am not that big on group/xp grinding (hence my 90AAs).  I can't provide a function in a group or raid without grinding hundreds of AAs, and then I feel the only AAs I can take are ones that keep me alive when charm breaks or mezz fails.  Why can't I spend some damn AAs on making sure THOSE don't fail.  Then I wouldn't have to feel useless in this game.
<br />

<br />
Fondest memory in EQ....  getting air elemental illusion and not being KOS in Befallen, and exploring the entire place, buffing groups as I came across them. 
<br />

<br />
Why can't this game give me that feeling back?
<br />

<br />
Account <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> renewed 9-23-04</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
