				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am considering canceling my account, but so far have not done so.  If I do so, it will probably be one where I cancel for a month and then come back - mainly to see if they have fixed things.
<br />

<br />
For me the biggest issue is that I have spent 27 hours in OOW zones and still have 0 spells (have seen 5 drop and lost rolls).  I also don't like it that level 69-70 spells can never be sold in the bazaar.  This frustration of not having my spells is my main reason for considering canceling.
<br />

<br />
I don't have my new charm spells yet, so can't really comment on them.  I definitely think it is the wrong thing to do.
<br />

<br />
I also think that the game has gotten too hard.  Having most spells on vendors, with a few quested, all sellable in bazaar, was just fine for me.  Having mobs that mage pets could tank was reasonable.  Fighting these behemoths that kill you when they sneeze, and then take down cities when you charm them are not good.  Scale back mob dps and you don't need a charm nerf.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I think that cc skills are useful in OOW and work reasonably well.  I don't have any of the new spells, so if there is no WoM or fascination upgrade, then I would be upset with that.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
