				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I haven't played for about 4 days now after trying to charm solo at WoS zoneline. 
<br />

<br />
I had 2 successfull runs, no breaks... had to nuke down ex-pet because it was too low to get another, that's fine. However, the 3rd and last time of the night I had a break, at 4% of target and 5% of pet, got summoned by both target and ex-pet and beat down before I could even get off one WoM. If I didn't NEED to haste my pet AND nuke AND end up rune tanking anyway in order to win by a SLIM margin even against a preslowed target... that would have been fun, it wasn't tho, and the exp I gained (barely) due to the death and down time made it clear charming in OoW was NOT an option.
<br />

<br />
I'm not happy, at all, that we get our buffs before our mezzes. Thanks for the message there.
<br />

<br />
I left my guild (we were working on inktu'ta when I left) 4 days before OoW went live because I wasn't having fun in the game, I thought it might be the guild, but it turned out to be a lot more. I wanted to see if getting time to solo and group without raiding obligations would bring life back into the game for me. It didn't. I have fun raiding, and when there are regularly 4 or more enchanters on a raid you start feeling reduntant pretty fast... and then you're told to let tanks tank mezz because of resists.
<br />

<br />
Of course I'm still steaming right now. Likely I'll re-enable my account after Black & White, Civ3, and a few other old RTS games of mine (and console games) get old again. But right now I'm finding more enjoyment tossing villagers that represent Brenlo and others in a high arch out into the ocean while playing Black & White <img src="images/smiles/boxer.gif" alt="Boxer" border="0" /> 
