				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'll be cancelling when I get off work oct 5th, got two accounts. I'll take a few weeks and revisit all the zones I grew up charming in. I've spent over a year building up this chanter, not long I know compared to some of the history that you other chanters have. 
<br />

<br />
I also played for about 8 months when Kunark first went live another chanter, did not charm as much them but I had tasted a piece of heaven that first time playing and that feeling never left me. As soon as I hit level 12 my second time around I loaded charm and its never left my line up, ever. Slowly but surely I perfected my charming skills I would stun on breaks as a young chanter because everyone had kei, my breeze or clarity would stick on no one, although a lot of nice sowers would hit me with it after I tried to clarity them.  I could not afford to buy sow potions either, heck I didn't even know about pok/bazaar first couple months I started playing again. 
<br />

<br />
Charm soloing or douing is everything that makes this game fun for me, Everquest is the only online game I have ever played and will probably always be the only one I ever play. I'm a strategy gamer for the most part and was just a fluke one day that I ended up watching someone play this game in one of those pay by the hour places. Three of us went in there to play some RTS game against one another and the guy behind the desk happened to be playing eq. I asked a few questions about it, before I knew it he was telling me all about it. He seemed so exited I just kept thinking wow must be a cool game for the guy to be this worked up over it.  So i bought it and the rest is history. 
<br />

<br />
So here I am now lvl 65 75 aas and feeling totally lost. I know this will eventually affect Cod too the spell I've been dreaming of for so long. Finally the day I aquired it I paid way over normal but I wanted it soooo bad. I felt so complete when I loaded it that first time. Now even thinking of charm since this nerf gives me a sick feeling in my stomach. 
<br />

<br />
Thanks all for everything I mainly always lurked but the Runes and the chanter boards on everquest realms taught me alot about being a good chanter. 
<br />

