			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Started playing in late 1998, started as a druid, and after a year of playing decided i wanted an enchanter for "clarity" at all times.. 
<br />

<br />
As you may have guessed my enchanter quickly became my main.  I loved CC'ing everywhere I went.  As luclin came out I found it a little harder to keep up with the raids and key's an what not, so i fell behind to exp groups.  PoP came out and again, i could not afford to fork out that much money (for both accounts) and waited 8 months to get pop.  By the time I did, most of my friends were flagged and had left me behind.  I never was able to get elemental flagged, and after watching my brother buy GoD to start a bezerker, and become utterly frustrated with sony's attitude after releaseing a uncompleted expansion.. We quit.  I have been gone a while, and came back to see what all the fuss over OoW was about.  In the last few years I have aquired many of my friends accounts.. and for a while i was 6 boxing.. for the sheer reason it was impossible to get a group to stay together.  
<br />

<br />
I activated my enchanter and bought OoW, only to find that sony has again just give the big middle finger to all of it's loyal players.  Nicly done sony, no more sony discman for me.  *or anything else sony puts thier hands on*
<br />

<br />
My gripes:
<br />
- expansions:  Why is that new players get evolutions, and veterans of the game get to pay full price for every expansion sony releases every 8 months (which doesn't add anything to gameplay, only 1 or 2 things that make you want to buy it)
<br />
- Nerfs: no need to mention them, they've all been covered
<br />
- Fun: Playing eq is no longer fun.  Back in KC, SoV zones, even pop to a point, CC'ing was fun, and a challenge.. but then they released more and more "uber" gear which allowed enhanters to function on gear alone, rather than skill.   I saw so many enchanters spring up on the server to become buff-bots, kei sluts, or whatnot.  The game just isn't want it used to be.
<br />
- Bugs: Only reason I ever started EQ was because out of the other MMRPG's of the time, it was the least buggy, and ran smoothly.  Now the engian is overworked, they contiune to push things in the game without programming them correctly.  I am tired of patching for an expansion only to find half of the *$&# in the game broken.
<br />
- Cost:  Paying for 2-4 accounts at a time is an ungodly cost, but bearable if thats what you want to do.. however, buying 4 sets of expansions is unreal.  I've been playing Eve-online latly, and they do not charge for expansions, only monthly fee's.  This is how it SHOULD be done.  But again, sony is a giant greedy corp that only wants our money and does not care anything about any one of us.
<br />
- AA's:  I'm really really sure I had more aa's when i logged out for the last time just after GoD came out, than I did when i logged in just after OoW came out.  Anyone care to explain?  Asked sony and they said I was obviously mistaken.  Perhaps I was, until i looked at my magelo account, which i was avid at keeping up to date.  Yep, I'm missing about 20 aa points, and i'm not sure from where..  At this point, really don't care to even find out where.
<br />
- Epic:  After seeing the new "epic" i'm through.  I've delt with the nerfts, the glitchs, everything else.  But a) to include GoD in the epic quest, which is hands down the worst expansion of all time, with LoY a close 2nd to worst.. that really urked me.  And then to see the focus/effect?  Nice.  The stats are ok, but not worth that kind of pain.  And i'm sorry If my mez breaks, or resists.. i'll deal with it.. but the last thing i need is less agro on it.  I do have a spell to lower agro, which has a very short cast time.. that is if it still works... And yet another rune?? I have eldtrich rune, and even IF the run was instant cast.. I don't give a $*&# They could have come up with something a little more useful to our class.  At the very least they could have named it something interesting... The protection of Eye.  Thanks again sony.
<br />

<br />
I really enjoyed my friends in EQ, and my guild that I lead.. but now i'm done.  And i Hope EQ2 crashes and burns.
<br />

<br />
-- Retired --
<br />
65 Enchanter
<br />
65 Warrior
<br />
65 Cleric
<br />
65 Druid
<br />
65 Rogue
<br />
64 Monk
<br />
59 SK
<br />
44 Bezerker
<br />

<br />
*yes, all on different accounts*
<br />

<br />
-Manatoya</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
