				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Canceled my account last night, for reasons that have already been listed time and time again.  
<br />

<br />
Ever since post vxed/tipt GoD (my guild was in inktu`ta, at least the last time we raided GoD that I was even inclined to play) I haven't had the least motivation to do the AA grind, and raiding had lost it's appeal as well...I thought OoW might change all of that, but I have been more than disappointed by what has happened.  
<br />

<br />
I miss the good old days, with a great group of good friends, camping the upper zone out in Old Sebilis, just because there were so many trains there that the XP beat just about anything else you could do, if you had people who could handle it. 
<br />

<br />
Seriously, this was the LAST thing that I expected from SoE.  I was thinking of trying out EQ2 when it came out, but after what they have pulled here, there's no way in hell.  Grats SoE, you have improved in pissing customers off (255)!!!
<br />

